This paper discusses the theoretical analysis of the support vector machine with random features, which is a popular method in machine learning. The paper focuses on the learning rate and optimization of the method, which are topics typically studied in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses experiments on a synthetic data set, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of feature selection methods and optimization techniques also suggests the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
